During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics, including the improved trade agreement with South Korea, the revised fourth quarter GDP numbers, and the President's upcoming remarks on infrastructure. She also addressed questions about pardons in the Russia probe, the Stormy Daniels case, police shootings, North Korea, and Amazon. Sanders reiterated the President's support for law enforcement, his desire for a level playing field in business, and his commitment to keeping the country safe. She also mentioned the administration's focus on workforce development and the need for Democrats to work on a long-term solution for DACA.